			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: left;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="620" height="350" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=29124790&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=00adef&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="620" height="350" src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=29124790&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=00adef&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object></p>
<p>Tomorrow marks the first of our 3 <em>Local Social Digital</em> fringe events at the 2011 Party Conferences.</p>
<p>The internet has had a huge impact on the way we live our lives, but have politicians and others responsible for delivering public services made the most of this? At our Local Social Digital sessions our speakers and audience members will share examples of how the web can be used to achieve a more open and engaging political system.</p>
<p>To give you a better idea of why <a href="http://wearefuturegov.com">FutureGov</a>, <a href="http://www.opm.co.uk/">OPM</a> and <a href="http://www.onroadmedia.org.uk/">On Road Media</a> have got involved in the party fringe programme and what Local Social Digital means to us, we&#8217;ve put together a short video to explain all. Take a look and let us know what you think.</p>
<p>Or better still, see you at the <a href="http://localsocialdigital.com">fringe events</a>.</p>
